HEADWORD: Synanthous
<hw>Syn*an"thous</hw> <pr>(s⟦icr⟧n*⟦acr⟧n"th⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>syn-</ets> + Gr. <grk>'a`nqos</grk> flower.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having flowers and leaves which appear at the
same time; -- said of certain plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

